## 1. Product Overview
 
Bunkai is a web-based Japanese language learning tool designed for professionals working in Japanese-speaking companies who can speak conversational Japanese but struggle to read kanji. It extracts vocabulary, grammar patterns, and key sentences from real workplace text (emails, chat messages, meeting notes) and converts them into structured Anki flashcards for spaced repetition study.
 
**Target User:** Non-native Japanese speakers (N3–N2 speaking level, N5 kanji reading level) working in Japanese corporate environments.
 
**Core Problem:** The friction between encountering unfamiliar Japanese text at work and actively learning that vocabulary is too high. Users procrastinate because the manual process of looking up words, creating flashcards, and maintaining a study routine is tedious.
 
**Solution:** Reduce the learning pipeline to a single paste action. Text goes in, structured learning cards come out, ready for Anki import.
 
