## 2. Technical Architecture
 
### 2.1 Two-Step Processing Pipeline
 
The system uses a two-step architecture to balance extraction completeness with enrichment depth.
 
#### Step 1: Extract (Lightweight, High Coverage)
 
- Single API call per text chunk (or single call for texts under 1,500 characters)
- Extracts ALL kanji words, ALL grammar patterns (every JLPT level), and 3–5 key sentences
- Compact output format: word, reading, meaning, JLPT level only
- No item cap — extracts everything found in the text
- Long texts are automatically chunked (~500 characters per chunk) and processed in parallel
- Results are deduplicated and merged across chunks
 
#### Step 2: Enrich (On-Demand, Per Item)
 
Enrichment is triggered by user interaction — clicking on a specific vocabulary word or sentence:
 
- **Vocabulary Enrichment:** Fetches 2–4 synonyms with nuance explanations, an example sentence with furigana, and a one-sentence nuance comparison tip.
- **Sentence Enrichment:** Generates full furigana annotation for every kanji, natural English translation, and highlights 3–6 key vocabulary words from the sentence.
 
This architecture ensures no vocabulary is missed during extraction (since the prompt is lightweight), while enrichment depth is unlimited (since it processes one item at a time and never truncates).
 
### 2.2 Text Chunking Strategy
 
- Splits on Japanese sentence endings (。！？), newlines, and periods
- Target chunk size: ~500 characters
- Chunks processed in batches of 3 (parallel)
- Results merged with deduplication by word/title/sentence
 
### 2.3 LLM Integration
 
| Call Type | Purpose | Model | Max Tokens |
|-----------|---------|-------|------------|
| Extract | Full vocab/grammar/sentence extraction | claude-sonnet-4 | 4,096 |
| Enrich Vocab | Synonyms, nuance, example | claude-sonnet-4 | 1,024 |
| Enrich Sentence | Furigana, translation, key vocab | claude-sonnet-4 | 1,024 |
 
### 2.4 Error Handling & Observability
 
- Every API call is wrapped in granular try-catch with step-by-step logging
- Debug log panel visible in the UI — shows request building, fetch status, response parsing, JSON repair attempts
- 60-second timeout with AbortController on extraction calls
- 45-second timeout on enrichment calls
- Automatic JSON repair for truncated responses (bracket closing, regex extraction of complete objects)
- Elapsed timer visible during loading
- Error/success lines color-coded in debug log (red/green)
 
