## 7. Primary User Flow
 
1. User receives a Japanese email or chat message at work.
2. Opens Bunkai, pastes the text, clicks Extract.
3. System extracts all vocabulary (sorted N5→N1), grammar patterns, and key sentences.
4. Known words are auto-dimmed and deselected. User sees "12 new · 5 known" summary.
5. User clicks "Load synonyms" on unfamiliar words to see related vocabulary with nuance tips.
6. User clicks "Load furigana" on interesting sentences to see full breakdown.
7. User optionally adds custom sentences from the same conversation.
8. User clicks "Add to Deck". New words are auto-tracked as Known.
9. User clicks "Export TSV", pastes into a .tsv file, imports into Anki.
10. User reviews cards in Anki using spaced repetition.
 
This flow can be repeated multiple times per day with near-zero friction — each iteration takes 30–60 seconds of active user time.
 
